<h2>How to Choose</h2>

<p>The right revenue intelligence platform depends on what you already have and what problem you are solving:</p>

<ul>
  <li><strong>You need better forecasts and already have Gong:</strong> Gong's Revenue Intelligence layer may be enough &mdash; no need for a second tool.</li>
  <li><strong>You need forecasting + call coaching and have neither:</strong> Gong gives you both in one. Clari + a separate call tool costs more.</li>
  <li><strong>You need pure forecasting accuracy and have clean CRM data:</strong> Clari is the focused choice. It does one thing better than anyone.</li>
  <li><strong>You want engagement + pipeline in one platform:</strong> Salesloft (mid-market) or Outreach (enterprise) with their built-in forecast modules.</li>
  <li><strong>You need custom forecasting models:</strong> Boostup gives RevOps teams the most control.</li>
  <li><strong>You want to bet on AI-native:</strong> Aviso is the most aggressive AI-first approach.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

<h3>Do I need revenue intelligence if I already have a CRM?</h3>
<p>CRM data alone does not forecast accurately because it depends on reps manually updating deal stages. Revenue intelligence tools capture signals automatically &mdash; email opens, call sentiment, meeting frequency &mdash; and use them to predict outcomes independently of rep self-reporting. Based on G2 reviews, teams using revenue intelligence alongside their CRM see 15-30% improvement in forecast accuracy.</p>

<h3>What is the difference between Gong and Clari?</h3>
<p>Gong started as conversation intelligence (call recording + coaching) and expanded into revenue forecasting. Clari started as a forecasting platform. Gong's revenue signals come from conversation data; Clari's come from CRM + activity data. If you need both call coaching and forecasting, Gong is the better all-in-one. If you only need forecasting, Clari is more focused.</p>

<h3>Are revenue intelligence tools worth the cost for small teams?</h3>
<p>Most revenue intelligence platforms are enterprise-priced ($50&ndash;130/seat/month) and require CRM integration setup. For teams under 20 reps, the ROI is harder to justify. Better options for smaller teams: HubSpot Sales Hub Pro ($100/seat/month) includes basic forecasting, or use Gong's Essential tier if call coaching is the primary need.</p>

